OL,3,CUnion calls on Chancellor to freeze
OL,4,Cduty on Scotch whisky
OL,6,FMs Gilmour said: "Vital steps can be
OL,7,Ftaken now to back Scotch whisky amidst
OL,8,Fglobal trade uncertainty whilst still
OL,9,Fprotecting public finances.
OL,11,F"A commitment to freeze excise duty
OL,12,Fthroughout this Parliament will
OL,13,Fprovide business confidence in a
OL,14,Fsector struggling under increased
OL,15,Ftariffs and taxation, while allowing
OL,16,Fthe benefits of the Government's
OL,17,Feconomic policies to reach our members
OL,18,Fon the shop floor."
